      <title>$100k worldwide Unity contest</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1315/posts/100k-worldwide-unity-contest/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 22 May 2014 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1315/posts/100k-worldwide-unity-contest/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://davevoyles.azurewebsites.net/4351/&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Unity Marketing&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;http://davevoyles.azurewebsites.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Unity-Marketing-1024x531.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, Unity and Microsoft announced a new &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;world-wide contest with $100K in prizes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; to bring Unity games to Windows and Windows Phone. The rules are pretty straight forward, and he contest site is hosted at &lt;a href=&#34;http://unity3d.com/contest/windows&#34;&gt;http://unity3d.com/contest/windows&lt;/a&gt;, so feel free to head over and submit your games!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
